{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Liu et al. [40] proposed SA-TrellisNet, a news-driven stock index prediction model that combines a CNN-LSTMbased sentiment analysis module with a sentiment attention mechanism and TrellisNet for accurate forecasting.",
    "Kirtac and Germano [41] evaluated the effectiveness of LLMs such as OPT, BERT, and FinBERT in analyzing financial news sentiment, finding that the GPT-3-based OPT model achieves 74.4% accuracy in predicting stock returns.",
    "A trading strategy using OPT yields a Sharpe ratio of 3.05 and a 355% return over two years, highlighting LLMs' potential in market forecasting and portfolio management.",
    "Mo et al. [42] applied sentiment analysis to financial news headlines using fine-tuned large language models, finding that the gemma-7b model achieves the best performance in classifying investor sentiment.A comparative study by Li et al.",
    "[22] evaluated the performance of sentiment analysis against other approaches such as bag-of-words and sentiment polarity."
  ],
